    "recap_headline": "University of Michigan Athletics",
    "recap_text": "\u00bb Michigan won 3-2 in its home opener against Western Michigan.\n\u00bb Four Wolverines tallied four hits in the contest with two doubles from\nEvan Haeger\n.\n\u00bb\nNoah Miller\nbrought home a pair of runners in the first inning to get the Wolverines off to a quick start.\n\u00bb\nSlade Moore\npitched 1.2 scoreless innings to pick up his first career win in relief.\nANN ARBOR, Mich.\n-- In its home opener, the University of Michigan baseball team defeated Western Michigan 3-2 on Tuesday afternoon (March 10) at the Wilpon Complex, home of Ray Fisher Stadium.\nMichigan (9-6) erased Western Michigan's brief lead in the bottom of the first with an RBI single from\nNoah Miller\nto score\nBrayden Jefferis\nand\nColby Turner\nto put the Wolverines ahead 2-1. Western Michigan tied the game at two in the top of the second with a two-out single.\nThe game remained deadlocked until the sixth, when\nEvan Haeger\nput the Wolverines in front with a bunt that scored\nCarson Luna\nfrom third to make the score 3-2.\nThe Broncos had chances to score throughout the game, stranding 13 runners, including three in the fourth and two in the seventh and eighth innings.\nIn the top of the ninth, WMU earned a leadoff walk, but a fielder's choice left the Broncos with a runner at first and one out.\nGavin DeVooght\ninduced a groundout that\nDrew Culbertson\nturned into a double play to end the game.\nFive Wolverines tallied two hits in the contest: Jefferis, Turner, Miller,\nMatthew Ossenfort\nand Haeger, while Miller tallied two RBI.\nPreston Barr\npitched 1.2 innings to start the game, and\nGrant Bradley\ncalmed the Broncos offense with 3.1 scoreless innings of relief.\nSlade Moore\npitched 1.2 innings, earning his first career win.\nMax Debiec\npitched a scoreless inning and DeVooght closed it out to earn his fifth save.\nMichigan will open Big Ten play on Friday (March 13), when the Wolverines battle No. 1 UCLA in the start of a three-game set against the Bruins at Jackie\u00a0Robinson Stadium. First pitch is set for 6 p.m. PT, and the game will be streamed live on B1G+."
